  "plan": "1) Update apt package lists so we can install packages. 2) Install a MySQL client (default-mysql-client) non-interactively. 3) Use the mysql client to attempt a connection as root with no password and run: SHOW DATABASES; — this will reveal available databases and confirm connectivity. If the install or connection fails, we'll inspect error output and adapt (e.g., provide credentials or look for a socket).",
